<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>TableXiMenuExercise</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body>

<h4>How to upload a student roster file:</h4>


<p>
  - Create the comma separated value (csv) file
</p>
<p>
  - Save it to your computer
</p>
<p>
  - The upload form is below. Click "Choose File" and select the file you created.
</p>
<p>
  - Once selected, click "Upload File".
</p>
<p>
  - You will be notified if the upload was successful or not.
</p>
<p>
  - Process complete!
</p>


<h4>Here is what your file would look like:</h4>

<img src="http://i.imgur.com/ZB7BXJs.png">

<br><br>

<h4>
  Here is the form:
</h4>

<%= form_tag 'teachers/upload', id: "upload", :multipart => true do %>
   <label for="file">Upload csv File</label> <%= file_field_tag "file" %>
   <%= submit_tag "Upload File", id: "save" %>
<% end %>

<%= yield %>

</body>
</html>
